# AI API Choices — Quick Reference

A concise guide to popular AI APIs you can integrate into your applications. Links go to official docs or curated lists.

---

## 1. OpenAI
- Models: GPT (chat/text), DALL·E (images), Whisper (speech-to-text).
- SDKs: JavaScript, Python, .NET, Java, Go, and more.
- Docs: https://platform.openai.com/docs/overview • Quickstart: https://platform.openai.com/docs/quickstart

---

## 2. Azure OpenAI Service
- Hosted OpenAI models inside Azure with enterprise-grade security.
- Supports REST endpoints (completions, chat, images) and Azure AD authentication.
- Docs: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/openai/reference

---

## 3. Google Gemini
- Multimodal LLM for text, images, audio, video, and structured output.
- Supports REST, SSE streaming, WebSocket, and batch endpoints.
- Docs: https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs

---

## 4. Hugging Face Inference API
- Access thousands of open-source models (NLP, vision, code, audio).
- Good for open-source flexibility and experimentation; free tier available.
- Browse: https://aicurator.io/free-ai-apis/

---

## 5. Anthropic (Claude)
- Focused on safety, alignment, and reliable conversational behavior.
- Competitive for chat, coding, and reasoning tasks.
- Overview: https://dev.to/akshaymittal143/14-ai-apis-every-developer-should-know-in-2025-k96

---

## 6. AssemblyAI (Speech-to-Text)
- High-accuracy transcription, speaker diarization, sentiment insight.
- Best for audio analytics and transcription workflows.

---

## 7. Google Cloud AI & Vertex AI
- Full-stack services: vision, translation, speech, TTS, AutoML.
- Free trial credits available for new users.
- Listing: https://topbusinesssoftware.com/categories/artificial-intelligence-ai-apis/

---

## 8. Free / Low-cost Options
- OpenRouter, Replicate, Mistral, Ollama, Together AI, RunPod — good free tiers or local deploys.
- Curated list: https://aicurator.io/free-ai-apis/

---

## Choosing the Right API
- For advanced chat or text generation → OpenAI / Azure OpenAI  
- For multimodal & enterprise needs → Google Gemini  
- For open-source models & customization → Hugging Face  
- For voice-to-text → AssemblyAI or Google Speech-to-Text  
- For low-cost experimentation → OpenRouter, Replicate, Mistral, Ollama, Together AI

---

## Next steps
1. Open the docs for APIs you like.
2. Sign up to obtain keys and review pricing.
3. Try quickstart examples in your preferred stack.

